{"title_page": "Wonder Woman 1984", "text_new": "{{short description|Upcoming American superhero film}}\n{{Use American English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Wonder Woman 1984\n| image          = Wonder Woman 1984 poster.jpg\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Teaser poster\n| director       = [[Patty Jenkins]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Charles Roven]]\n* [[Deborah Snyder]]\n* [[Zack Snyder]]\n* [[Patty Jenkins]]\n* [[Gal Gadot]]\n* Stephen Jones\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* Patty Jenkins\n* [[Geoff Johns]]\n* [[David Callaham]]\n}}\n| story          = {{Plainlist|\n* Patty Jenkins\n* Geoff Johns\n}}\n| based_on       = {{Based on|[[Wonder Woman]]|[[William Moulton Marston]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://findawriter.wgaeast.org/project/1152284/wonder-woman-1984 |title=Wonder Woman 1984 \n|website=findawriter.wgaeast.org |accessdate=February 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Gal Gadot]]\n* [[Chris Pine]]\n* [[Kristen Wiig]]\n* [[Pedro Pascal]]\n* [[Robin Wright]]\n* [[Connie Nielsen]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Hans Zimmer]]\n| cinematography = [[Matthew Jensen (cinematographer)|Matthew Jensen]]\n| editing        = [[Richard Pearson (film editor)|Richard Pearson]]\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[DC Films]]\n* [[Atlas Entertainment]]\n* [[The Stone Quarry]]\n* [[Mad Ghost Productions]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.madghostproductions.com/category/film/ |title=Film \u2013 Mad Ghost Productions \n|website=www.madghostproductions.com |accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614005756/http://www.madghostproductions.com/category/film/|archive-date=June 14, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Warner Bros. Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|8|14|United States}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $175 million<ref name=WrapStream>{{cite web |url= https://www.thewrap.com/wonder-woman-1984-streaming-no-theater-warner-bros/ |title= Warner Bros Debates Whether \u2018Wonder Woman 1984\u2019 Should Skip Theaters for Streaming (Exclusive)|website=[[TheWrap]] |date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Wonder Woman 1984''''' (also marketed as '''''WW84: Wonder Woman 1984''''') is an upcoming American [[superhero film]] based on the [[DC Comics]] character [[Wonder Woman]]. It is the sequel to 2017's ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'' and the ninth installment in the [[DC Extended Universe]] (DCEU). The film is directed by [[Patty Jenkins]] from a script she wrote with [[Geoff Johns]] and [[David Callaham]], and a story by Johns and Jenkins, and stars [[Gal Gadot]] as Diana Prince/Wonder Woman, alongside [[Chris Pine]], [[Kristen Wiig]], [[Pedro Pascal]], [[Robin Wright]], and [[Connie Nielsen]] in supporting roles. Set in 1984, the film follows Diana as she faces off against [[Maxwell Lord]] and [[Cheetah (comics)|Cheetah]].\n\nDiscussion of a sequel began shortly after the release of the first film in June 2017, and the decision to proceed was confirmed the following month. Principal photography began on June 13, 2018\u2014with filming taking place at [[Warner Bros. Studios, Leavesden]] in England, as well as the District of Columbia and Northern Virginia in the United States, London and Duxford in England, Tenerife and Fuerteventura in the Canary Islands, and Almer\u00eda in Andalusia, Spain\u2014and wrapped on December 22, 2018, after a six-month shoot. Additional filming took place in July 2019.\n\n''Wonder Woman 1984'' is scheduled to be released in the United States by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] in [[RealD 3D]], [[Dolby Cinema]], [[IMAX]], and [[IMAX 3D]] on August 14, 2020.\n\n==Premise==\nIn 1984, [[Wonder Woman|Diana Prince]] comes into conflict with two formidable foes - media businessman [[Maxwell Lord]] and friend-turned-enemy [[Cheetah (comics)|Barbara Ann Minerva/Cheetah]] - while reuniting with her lover, [[Steve Trevor]].<ref name=\"ColdWar\">{{cite web |url=https://amp.pastemagazine.com/articles/2017/07/wonder-woman-2-may-be-set-during-the-cold-war-and.html |title=Report: Wonder Woman 2 Set During the Cold War, Chris Pine to Return |website=amp.pastemagazine |date=July 11, 2017|access-date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626101027/https://amp.pastemagazine.com/articles/2017/07/wonder-woman-2-may-be-set-during-the-cold-war-and.html|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Cheetah confirmation\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Gal Gadot]] as [[Wonder Woman|Diana Prince/Wonder Woman]]: An immortal [[Demigod|demigoddess]], [[Amazons (DC Comics)|Amazon]] princess and warrior. Diana is the daughter of [[Hippolyta (DC Comics)|Hippolyta]], the Amazonian queen of [[Themyscira (DC Comics)|Themyscira]] and [[Zeus (DC Comics)|Zeus]], the king of the [[Olympian Gods (DC Comics)|Olympian Gods]].<ref name=\"Sequel-RT\"/>\n*[[Chris Pine]] as [[Steve Trevor]]: An American pilot and the love interest of Diana, who had presumably died during the events of [[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|the first film]].<ref name=\"WW84Title\">{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/06/wonder-woman-1984-first-look-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-chris-pine-1201974200/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' First Look: Gal Gadot and Patty Jenkins Reunite, While Chris Pine Makes Surprise Return |last=Sharf |first=Zack |publisher=[[IndieWire]] |date=June 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 13, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620123231/http://www.indiewire.com/2018/06/wonder-woman-1984-first-look-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-chris-pine-1201974200/ |archive-date=June 20, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Kristen Wiig]] as [[Cheetah (comics)|Barbara Ann Minerva/Cheetah]]: An [[Archaeology|archaeologist]] who befriends Diana before becoming imbued with a [[Cheetah|cheetah]]-like appearance and abilities.<ref name=\"WiigCast\"/><ref name=\"Cheetah confirmation\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Newby |first1=Richard |title=The Bad Guys Are Inheriting the DC Universe |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dc-movie-universe-is-going-villains-1118179 |accessdate=June 11, 2018 |date=June 8, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612145329/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dc-movie-universe-is-going-villains-1118179 |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Pedro Pascal]] as [[Maxwell Lord|Maxwell \"Max\" Lord]]: A media businessman and entrepreneur who is famous for TV [[Infomercial|infomercials]].<ref name=\"PascalCast\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Pantozzi |first1=Jill |title=Pedro Pascal's Wonder Woman 1984 Character Is Exactly Who You Thought He Was |url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/pedro-pascals-wonder-woman-1984-character-is-exactly-wh-1839321290 |accessdate=October 24, 2019 |work=Gizmodo |date=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Robin Wright]] as [[Antiope (comics)|Antiope]]: Hippolyta's deceased sister, general of the Amazon army and Diana's aunt.<ref name=\"NielsenWright\"/>\n*[[Connie Nielsen]] as [[Hippolyta (DC Comics)|Hippolyta]]: The queen of [[Themyscira (DC Comics)|Themyscira]] and Diana's mother.<ref name=\"NielsenWright\"/>\n\nAdditionally, [[Natasha Rothwell]], [[Ravi Patel (actor)|Ravi Patel]], [[Gabriella Wilde]], [[Kristoffer Polaha]] and [[Amr Waked]] have been cast in undisclosed roles.<ref name=\"Rothwell\">{{cite news |last1=Galuppo |first1=Mia |title=''Insecure'' Star Natasha Rothwell Joins ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/natasha-rothwell-joins-wonder-woman-1984-1129667 |accessdate=July 29, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=July 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725044002/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/natasha-rothwell-joins-wonder-woman-1984-1129667|archive-date=July 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"PatelWilde\">{{cite news |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=Ravi Patel & Gabriella Wilde Boarding ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/wonder-woman-1984-casting-ravi-patel-1202435167/ |accessdate=July 29, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=July 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729085835/https://deadline.com/2018/07/wonder-woman-1984-casting-ravi-patel-1202435167/|archive-date=July 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Polaha\">{{cite news |last1=Polaha |first1=Kristoffer |title=Why I Love Doing Hallmark Movies, an Actor's Confession (Guest Column) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/why-i-love-doing-hallmark-movies-an-actors-confession-guest-column-1163165 |accessdate=November 21, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=November 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181121194830/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/why-i-love-doing-hallmark-movies-an-actors-confession-guest-column-1163165|archive-date=November 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/amrwaked/status/1195801138928504837|title=\u0627\u0646\u062a\u0638\u0631\u0648\u0627 \u0638\u0647\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0641\u064a \u0641\u064a\u0644\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u0623\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u0627\u0631\u0642\u0629 \u0661\u0669\u0668\u0664 (\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0632\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u062b\u0627\u0646\u064a) \u0625\u062e\u0631\u0627\u062c \u0628\u0627\u062a\u064a \u062c\u064a\u0646\u0643\u064a\u0646\u0632 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u062a\u0648\u0642\u0639 \u0646\u0632\u0648\u0644\u0647 \u0641\u064a \u064a\u0648\u0646\u064a\u0648 \u0662\u0660\u0662\u0660. \u064a\u0627 \u0631\u0628 \u064a\u0639\u062c\u0628\u0643\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u064a\u0644\u0645.|first=Amr|last=Waked|date=November 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n[[Gal Gadot]], who originally signed for three feature films with ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'' being her second, had extended her contract beyond that.<ref name=\"Sequel-RT\">{{cite web |last1=Schmitz |first1=Greg Dean |title=''Wonder Woman'' Sequel Details Emerge, And More Movie News |url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/article/wonder-woman-sequel-details-emerge-and-more-movie-news/ |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |date=June 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170724160242/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2017/07/24/wonder-woman-sequel-title-revealed.html|archive-date=July 24, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The director of the first film, [[Patty Jenkins]], who initially signed for only one film, had expressed interest in returning to direct the sequel.<ref name=\"SignedOnlyOne\">{{cite web |last1=Kit |first1=Bory |title=''Wonder Woman'' Director Patty Jenkins Not Signed for Sequel |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-director-patty-jenkins-not-signed-sequel-1010845 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |date=June 7, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611065039/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-director-patty-jenkins-not-signed-sequel-1010845|archive-date=June 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"ToAmerica\">{{cite web |last1=Goldberg |first1=Matt |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Setting Will Take Diana To America |url=https://collider.com/wonder-woman-2-setting/ |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |date=June 5, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170605201447/http://collider.com/wonder-woman-2-setting/|archive-date=June 5, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2017, during an interview with ''Variety'', comic book writer [[Geoff Johns]] revealed that he and Jenkins had started writing the treatment for a ''Wonder Woman'' sequel and that he had a \"cool idea for the second one\".<ref name=\"GeoffJohnsAboutSequel\">{{cite news |last1=Lang |first1=Brent |title=DC Film's Jon Berg, Geoff Johns on Success of ''Wonder Woman'' and Sequel Plans (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/jon-berg-geoff-johns-wonder-woman-sequel-justice-league-1202471557/ |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |work=Variety |date=June 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701022527/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/jon-berg-geoff-johns-wonder-woman-sequel-justice-league-1202471557/|archive-date=July 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"JenkinsWriting\">{{cite news |last1=Nyren |first1=Erin |title=Patty Jenkins Developing ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/wonder-woman-sequel-patty-jenkins-1202472855/ |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |work=Variety |date=June 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170620221847/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/wonder-woman-sequel-patty-jenkins-1202472855/|archive-date=June 20, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> While speaking in a Q&A at a Women in Film screening of the film, Jenkins confirmed she would indeed direct the sequel.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sobel |first1=Ariel |title=BREAKING: Patty Jenkins Confirms She's Directing the ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel |url=https://www.advocate.com/film/2017/6/29/breaking-patty-jenkins-confirms-shes-directing-wonder-woman-sequel |website=Advocate |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |date=June 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630072821/https://www.advocate.com/film/2017/6/29/breaking-patty-jenkins-confirms-shes-directing-wonder-woman-sequel|archive-date=June 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> However, Jenkins later tweeted that \"it wasn't a confirmation. Just talking about ideas and hopes\".<ref name=\"JenkinsBacktracks\">{{cite news |last1=Wood |first1=Matt |title=Patty Jenkins Backtracks Her ''Wonder Woman 2'' Confirmation |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1676140/patty-jenkins-backtracks-wonder-woman-2-confirmation |accessdate=July 23, 2017 |work=CinemaBlend |date=June 30, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804121758/http://www.cinemablend.com/news/1676140/patty-jenkins-backtracks-wonder-woman-2-confirmation|archive-date=August 4, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn July 22, 2017, at [[San Diego Comic-Con]], the studio officially announced a sequel would be produced, with Jenkins returning as director; its title was listed as ''Wonder Woman 2''.<ref name=\"OfficiallyAnnouncedCC\">{{cite news |last1=Freeman |first1=Molly |title=Warner Bros. Officially Announces ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel |url=https://screenrant.com/wonder-woman-2-sequel-confirmed-warner-bros/ |accessdate=July 23, 2017 |work=Screen Rant |date=July 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723065320/http://screenrant.com/wonder-woman-2-sequel-confirmed-warner-bros/|archive-date=July 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"TitleComicCon\">{{cite news |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=Warner Bros Confirms DC Universe Pic Titles: ''Wonder Woman II'', ''Flashpoint'' & More \u2013 Comic-Con |url=https://deadline.com/2017/07/wonder-woman-ii-flashpoint-1202133919/ |accessdate=July 23, 2017 |work=Deadline |date=July 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722235732/http://deadline.com/2017/07/wonder-woman-ii-flashpoint-1202133919/|archive-date=July 22, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In September 2017, it was officially confirmed that Jenkins would be directing the sequel.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sharf |first1=Zack |title=''Wonder Woman 2'': Patty Jenkins Signing Historic Deal to Become Highest Paid Female Director in Hollywood |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/wonder-woman-2-patty-jenkins-director-highest-paid-female-1201867661/ |accessdate=September 11, 2017 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=September 11, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911073253/http://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/wonder-woman-2-patty-jenkins-director-highest-paid-female-1201867661/|archive-date=September 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On September 13, 2017, it was reported that ''[[The Expendables (2010 film)|The Expendables]]'' writer [[David Callaham]] would join the film to co-write the script with Jenkins and Johns, who were already working on it for several months.<ref name=\"CallahamWriting\">{{cite news |last1=Kit |first1=Borys |title=''The Expendables'' Writer Joins Patty Jenkins, Geoff Johns to Write ''Wonder Woman 2'' (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/expendables-writer-dave-callaham-joins-wonder-woman-2-writing-team-1038759 |accessdate=September 20, 2017 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=September 13, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170919042419/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/expendables-writer-dave-callaham-joins-wonder-woman-2-writing-team-1038759|archive-date=September 19, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\nOn February 28, 2018, it was reported that the film would be shot with [[IMAX]] film cameras in select action sequences.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/money/news/imax-imax-q4-2017-results-earnings-call-transcript/ar-BBJGs2A |title=IMAX (IMAX) Q4 2017 Results \u2013 Earnings Call Transcript |date=February 28, 2018 |accessdate=June 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614095003/https://www.msn.com/en-us/money/news/imax-imax-q4-2017-results-earnings-call-transcript/ar-BBJGs2A|archive-date=June 14, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> By late May 2018, long-time DCEU producer [[Zack Snyder]] confirmed on social media platform [[Vero (app)|Vero]] that he, along with his wife [[Deborah Snyder]], would serve as producers on the ''Wonder Woman'' sequel.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/updates-on-incredibles-2-supergirl-the-expanse-and-m-1826469809 |title=Updates On ''Incredibles 2'', ''Supergirl'', ''The Expanse'', and More |last=Whitbrook |first=James |work=io9 |access-date=June 6, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180605152007/https://io9.gizmodo.com/updates-on-incredibles-2-supergirl-the-expanse-and-m-1826469809 |archive-date=June 5, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> On June 13, 2018, the title of the film was announced to be ''Wonder Woman 1984''.<ref name=\"WW84Title\"/> A source close to Jenkins described it as a stand-alone film \"in the same way that ''[[Indiana Jones (franchise)|Indiana Jones]]'' or ''[[Production of the James Bond films|[James] Bond]]'' films are, instead of one continuous story that requires many installments.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/03/wonder-woman-1984-not-a-sequel-1202051300/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' Is 'Not a Sequel' |last=Nordine |first=Michael |date=March 15, 2019 |website=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=March 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Pre-production===\nPre-production officially began by early December 2017 in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web |last=Nambiar |first=Smitha |url=http://pursuenews.com/director-patty-jenkins-confirms-wonder-woman-2-pre-production/ |date=December 6, 2017|access-date=December 6, 2017 |title=Director Patty Jenkins Confirms ''Wonder Woman 2'' Is in Pre-Production |website=PursueNews.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210195120/http://pursuenews.com/director-patty-jenkins-confirms-wonder-woman-2-pre-production|archive-date=December 10, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> That same month, director Patty Jenkins stated that the film would be another great love story.<ref>{{cite web |last=Daly |first=Rhian |url=https://www.nme.com/news/film/director-patty-jenkins-teases-details-wonder-woman-2-storyline-2167289/ |date=December 1, 2017 |accessdate=December 1, 2017 |title=Director Patty Jenkins teases more details of ''Wonder Woman 2'' storyline |website=[[NME]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201221520/http://www.nme.com/news/film/director-patty-jenkins-teases-details-wonder-woman-2-storyline-2167289|archive-date=December 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2018, the film was confirmed to be set in the 1980s.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/wonder-woman-2-setting-patty-jenkins/ |title=Patty Jenkins Confirms ''Wonder Woman 2'' Is Set in The '80s |last=Stauffer |first=Derek |date=April 24, 2018 |publisher=ScreenRant |accessdate=April 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180425163050/https://screenrant.com/wonder-woman-2-setting-patty-jenkins/|archive-date=April 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The next month, production designer [[Aline Bonetto]] (''[[Am\u00e9lie]]'', ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'') was announced to be returning for the sequel, as well as [[Academy Award]] winner [[Lindy Hemming]], also returning as costume designer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://omegaunderground.com/2018/05/21/production-designer-aline-bonetto-returns-for-woman-woman-2/ |title=Production Designer Aline Bonetto Returns For ''Woman Woman 2'' |last=Williams |first=Caleb |date=May 21, 2018 |publisher=OmegaGround |accessdate=May 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613184634/https://omegaunderground.com/2018/05/21/production-designer-aline-bonetto-returns-for-woman-woman-2/|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn September 2017, Gal Gadot was confirmed to return as the title character.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=Patty Jenkins Closes Deal to Direct ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/patty-jenkins-wonder-woman-sequel-director-1202548413/ |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=May 29, 2018 |date=September 11, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911215145/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/patty-jenkins-wonder-woman-sequel-director-1202548413/ |archive-date=September 11, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> On February 28, 2018, it was reported that [[Kristen Wiig]] was in talks with the studio to play [[Cheetah (comics)|Cheetah]], the main villain of the film,<ref name=\"WiigCast\">{{cite news |last1=Jr |first1=Mike Fleming |title=Kristen Wiig Being Lassoed For Villain Role On ''Wonder Woman 2'' |url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/kristen-wiig-wonder-woman-2-cheetah-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-villain2-1202306419/ |accessdate=March 2, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=February 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310040404/https://deadline.com/2018/02/kristen-wiig-wonder-woman-2-cheetah-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-villain2-1202306419/|archive-date=March 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> with director Patty Jenkins confirming her casting the next month.<ref name=\"Cheetah confirmation\">{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2018/03/09/kristen-wiig-will-star-in-wonder-woman-sequel-as-the-cheetah-patty-jenkins-confirms/ |title=Kristen Wiig will star in ''Wonder Woman'' sequel as the Cheetah, Patty Jenkins confirms |date=March 9, 2018 |first=David |last=Betancourt |work=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=June 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310135642/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2018/03/09/kristen-wiig-will-star-in-wonder-woman-sequel-as-the-cheetah-patty-jenkins-confirms/|archive-date=March 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> By March 28, [[Pedro Pascal]], who played [[Ed Indelicato]] in the pilot of the canceled [[Wonder Woman (2011 TV pilot)|2011 ''Wonder Woman'' television adaptation]], was cast in an undisclosed key role, later revealed to be [[Maxwell Lord]].<ref name=\"PascalCast\">{{cite news |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=''Narcos'' Star Pedro Pascal Lands Key Role in ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/ |accessdate=May 29, 2018 |work=Variety |date=March 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180329010138/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/|archive-date=March 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=McMillan |first1=Graeme |title='Wonder Woman 1984': Who Is Maxwell Lord? |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-1984-who-is-pedro-pascals-maxwell-lord-1249865 |accessdate=October 26, 2019 |work=TheHollywoodReporter |date=October 24, 2019}}</ref> On June 13, Jenkins confirmed the return of [[Chris Pine]] as Steve Trevor via [[Twitter]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://twitter.com/PattyJenks/status/1006884175532740608 |title=Patty Jenkins on Twitter |work=Twitter|access-date=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617152137/https://twitter.com/pattyjenks/status/1006884175532740608|archive-date=June 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On July 24, 2018, Natasha Rothwell was announced to be cast in an undisclosed role.<ref name=\"Rothwell\"/> A few days later, on July 27, [[Ravi Patel (actor)|Ravi Patel]] and [[Gabriella Wilde]] also joined the film, with their roles being kept under wraps as well.<ref name=\"PatelWilde\"/> By late August, [[Connie Nielsen]] and [[Robin Wright]] were confirmed to reprise their roles as [[Hippolyta (DC Comics)|Hippolyta]] and [[Antiope (comics)|Antiope]] in a flashback sequence.<ref name=\"NielsenWright\">{{cite news |title=The Good Fight with Robin Wright |url=https://www.net-a-porter.com/us/en/porter/article-b36c5430c852c9af |accessdate=September 1, 2018 |work=Net-A-Porter |date=August 31, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831232242/https://www.net-a-porter.com/us/en/porter/article-b36c5430c852c9af|archive-date=August 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2018, [[Kristoffer Polaha]] revealed that he has a role in the film.<ref name=\"Polaha\"/>\n\n===Filming===\nPrincipal photography began on June 13, 2018, under the working title ''Magic Hour''.<ref name=\"Production\">{{cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180613005640/en/Cameras-Roll-Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-%E2%80%9CWonder-Woman |title=Cameras Roll on Warner Bros. Pictures' ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |work=Business Wire |date=June 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613234147/https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180613005640/en/Cameras-Roll-Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-%E2%80%9CWonder-Woman|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Filming took place at Warner Bros. Studios, Leavesden in England, and at a number of locations around the District of Columbia and Northern Virginia in the United States, including the [[Landmark Mall]] in Alexandria, Virginia and Georgetown during June and July 2018,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bizjournals.com/washington/news/2018/05/03/wonder-woman-2-to-film-at-alexandrias-deadlandmark.html |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' to film at Alexandria's dead Landmark Mall |last=Neibauer |first=Michael |date=May 3, 2018 |publisher=Washington Business Journal |accessdate=May 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-2-shooting-stateside-summer/ |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Reportedly Shooting Stateside This Summer |last=Villaverde |first=Noah |date=March 18, 2018 |website=Heroichollywood.com |accessdate=March 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320111741/https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-2-shooting-stateside-summer/|archive-date=March 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://georgetownmetropolitan.com/2018/05/24/wonder-woman-2-to-film-in-georgetown/ |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' to Film in Georgetown |date=May 24, 2018 |publisher=The Georgetown Metropolitan |accessdate=June 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143852/https://georgetownmetropolitan.com/2018/05/24/wonder-woman-2-to-film-in-georgetown/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> with scenes shot in Alexandria from June 18 through July 14.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/wonder-woman-2-starring-gal-gadot-open-casting-call/ |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Starring Gal Gadot Open Casting Call |date=June 14, 2018 |website=ProjectCasting.com |accessdate=June 16, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616130440/http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/wonder-woman-2-starring-gal-gadot-open-casting-call/|archive-date=June 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Filming occurred outside the U.S. Capitol in Washington, D.C., during mid-June.{{cn|date=February 2020}} Other filming locations around D.C. included the [[Penn Quarter]] neighborhood, [[McPherson Square]], the [[DAR Constitution Hall]] near the [[White House]], the [[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]] ([[Smithsonian Institution|Smithsonian]]), and the [[Lincoln Memorial]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fox5dc.com/news/local-news/-wonder-woman-continues-to-impact-traffic-around-dc-road-closures-in-penn-quarter |title=''Wonder Woman'' continues to impact traffic around DC, road closures in Penn Quarter |date=June 17, 2018 |website=Fox5dc.com |access-date=July 7, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707202222/http://www.fox5dc.com/news/local-news/-wonder-woman-continues-to-impact-traffic-around-dc-road-closures-in-penn-quarter |archive-date=July 7, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fox5dc.com/news/local-news/filming-for-rumored-wonder-woman-sequel-shutting-down-several-streets-around-mcpherson-square |title=Filming shutting down several streets around McPherson Square this weekend |date=July 6, 2018 |website=Fox5dc.com |accessdate=July 7, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707171636/http://www.fox5dc.com/news/local-news/filming-for-rumored-wonder-woman-sequel-shutting-down-several-streets-around-mcpherson-square|archive-date=July 7, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/fantasy-and-reality-clash-as-movie-makers-film-wonder-woman-in-dc/2018/07/07/4f044522-8215-11e8-b9a5-7e1c013f8c33_story.html |title=Fantasy and reality clash as movie makers film ''Wonder Woman'' in D.C. |last=Ruane |first=Michael E. |date=July 7, 2018 |publisher=The Washington Post|access-date=July 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711060118/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/fantasy-and-reality-clash-as-movie-makers-film-wonder-woman-in-dc/2018/07/07/4f044522-8215-11e8-b9a5-7e1c013f8c33_story.html|archive-date=July 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> By mid-July, production in the United States was completed and moved to England.<ref>{{cite web |last=Annerino |first=Mike |url=https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-pedro-pascal-filming/ |title=Pedro Pascal Heads To London To Film ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |date=July 13, 2018|access-date=July 29, 2018 |work=Heroic Hollywood|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729200532/https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-pedro-pascal-filming/|archive-date=July 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In August, filming on location took place in several places around London, including St. Andrew's Place, [[Regent's Park]] and the [[Royal College of Physicians]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Daniels |first=Omari |url=https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-1984-filming-london/ |title=New Set Photos Reveal ''Wonder Woman 1984'' Now Filming In London |date=August 7, 2018|access-date=August 9, 2018 |work=Heroic Hollywood|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810011451/https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-1984-filming-london/|archive-date=August 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Begley |first=Chris |url=https://batman-news.com/2018/08/09/wonder-woman-1984-to-film-at-royal-college-of-physicians-in-london-photo/ |title=Exclusive: ''Wonder Woman 1984'' to film at Royal College of Physicians in London (photo) |date=August 9, 2018|access-date=August 9, 2018 |work=Batman-News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810011233/https://batman-news.com/2018/08/09/wonder-woman-1984-to-film-at-royal-college-of-physicians-in-london-photo/|archive-date=August 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Between September and October 2018, production also took place at Almer\u00eda, in Andalusia, southern Spain,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.europapress.es/andalucia/almeria-00350/noticia-alcazaba-acogera-rodaje-varias-escenas-wonder-woman-1984-septiembre-20180828153022.html |title=La Alcazaba acoger\u00e1 el rodaje de varias escenas de ''Wonder Woman: 1984'' en septiembre |location=Almer\u00eda |date=August 28, 2018 |access-date=August 29, 2018 |newspaper=[[Europa Press (news agency)|Europa Press]] |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828152940/http://www.europapress.es/andalucia/almeria-00350/noticia-alcazaba-acogera-rodaje-varias-escenas-wonder-woman-1984-septiembre-20180828153022.html |archive-date=August 28, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.diariodealmeria.es/ocio/rodaje-Wonder-Woman-Alcazaba-septiembre_0_1277272371.html |title=El rodaje de ''Wonder Woman: 1984'' ser\u00e1 en la Alcazaba del 5 al 8 de septiembre |first=D. |last=Mart\u00ednez |date=August 29, 2018 |access-date=August 29, 2018 |newspaper=[[Diario de Almer\u00eda]] |language=es |publisher=[[Joly Digital]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829175350/https://www.diariodealmeria.es/ocio/rodaje-Wonder-Woman-Alcazaba-septiembre_0_1277272371.html |archive-date=August 29, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> as well as Fuerteventura and Tenerife in the Canary Islands.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/el-rodaje-de-wonder-woman-desembarca-a-finales-del-verano-MH4584385 |title=El rodaje de ''Wonder Woman'' desembarca a finales del verano |last=Monserrat |first=David |date=May 19, 2018 |publisher=Canarias7 (in Spanish)|access-date=May 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522042253/https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/el-rodaje-de-wonder-woman-desembarca-a-finales-del-verano-MH4584385|archive-date=May 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.guidetocanaryislands.com/tenerife-will-be-one-of-the-filming-locations-for-the-next-wonder-woman-movie/ |title=Tenerife will be one of the filming locations for the next Wonder Woman movie |date=April 20, 2018 |accessdate=May 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143205/https://www.guidetocanaryislands.com/tenerife-will-be-one-of-the-filming-locations-for-the-next-wonder-woman-movie/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> From September 5 to 11, filming occurred at the [[Alcazaba of Almer\u00eda]] fortified complex and the Wall of Jayran in Almer\u00eda.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cope.es/actualidad/cultura/noticias/alcazaba-almeria-acogera-septiembre-parte-rodaje-wonder-woman-1984-20180828_252883 |title=Alcazaba de Almer\u00eda acoger\u00e1 en septiembre parte rodaje ''Wonder Woman: 1984'' |date=August 28, 2018 |publisher=COPE (in Spanish) |accessdate=August 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829142505/https://www.cope.es/actualidad/cultura/noticias/alcazaba-almeria-acogera-septiembre-parte-rodaje-wonder-woman-1984-20180828_252883|archive-date=August 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Production moved to Fuerteventura from September 13 through September 26, with the Corralejo Dunes National Park, Parque Holand\u00e9s, El Jablito, La Oliva and the Jand\u00eda Natural Park as filming locations.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/una-superproduccion-para-fuerteventura-FI3965430 |title=Una superproducci\u00f3n para Fuerteventura |last=Monserrat |first=David |date=March 25, 2018 |publisher=Canarias7 (in Spanish)|access-date=May 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180325124824/https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/una-superproduccion-para-fuerteventura-FI3965430|archive-date=March 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/wonder-woman-1984-arranca-el-rodaje-el-jueves-13-hasta-el-dia-25-BE5457131 |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' arranca el rodaje el Jueves 13 hasta el dia 25 |date=September 11, 2018 |publisher=Canarias7 (in Spanish) |accessdate=September 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911092206/https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/wonder-woman-1984-arranca-el-rodaje-el-jueves-13-hasta-el-dia-25-BE5457131|archive-date=September 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Filming in Tenerife began during the last week of September, lasting two weeks at various different locations on the island.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thinkspain.com/news-spain/30917/wonder-woman-1984-to-be-filmed-in-tenerife |title=Wonder Woman 1984 to be filmed in Tenerife |date=August 28, 2018 |publisher=thinkSPAIN |accessdate=September 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903045916/https://www.thinkspain.com/news-spain/30917/wonder-woman-1984-to-be-filmed-in-tenerife|archive-date=September 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.laopinion.es/cultura/2018/09/02/productora-islena-sur-film-trabajara/906706.html |title=La productora isle\u00f1a Sur Film trabajar\u00e1 en el rodaje en Espa\u00f1a de ''Wonder Woman'' |date=September 2, 2018 |publisher=La Opini\u00f3n de Tenefife (in Spanish) |accessdate=September 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180902121332/https://www.laopinion.es/cultura/2018/09/02/productora-islena-sur-film-trabajara/906706.html|archive-date=September 2, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nProduction went back to England in October, with shooting on location taking place at the [[Imperial War Museum Duxford|Imperial War Museum]] in Duxford, [[Hyde Park, London|Hyde Park]] and the Savoy Hotel in Central London, and [[Torrington Square]], adjacent to Birkbeck, University of London.{{cn|date=February 2020}} By mid-November 2018, [[Pedro Pascal]] finished filming his scenes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/star-wars-pedro-pascal-mandalorian-series-1203023818/ |title=''Star Wars'': Pedro Pascal to Lead ''The Mandalorian'' Series |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=November 13, 2018 |publisher=Variety |access-date=November 14, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114000343/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/star-wars-pedro-pascal-mandalorian-series-1203023818/ |archive-date=November 14, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> Principal photography wrapped on December 22, 2018, after a six-month shoot.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-1984-wrap-december/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' To Wrap Filming This December |last=Mistroff |first=Michael |date=September 4, 2018 |publisher=HeroicHollywood |access-date=September 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905102049/https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-1984-wrap-december/ |archive-date=September 5, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/wonder-woman-1984-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-warner-bros-dc-1202525495/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'': Gal Gadot Posts Heartfelt Message As Production Wraps |last=Ramos |first=Dino-Ray |date=December 23, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |access-date=December 24, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224041346/https://deadline.com/2018/12/wonder-woman-1984-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-warner-bros-dc-1202525495/ |archive-date=December 24, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> Additional photography began on July 28, 2019, in London at Warner Bros. Studios,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/amp/2019/07/28/wonder-woman-1984-movie-spoilers-2020-reshoots-dceu/ |title=Wonder Woman 1984 Reportedly Doing Reshoots |date=July 28, 2019|access-date=September 6, 2019 |website=comicbook.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906071050/https://comicbook.com/dc/amp/2019/07/28/wonder-woman-1984-movie-spoilers-2020-reshoots-dceu/|archive-date=September 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and was completed the following month.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.unionjournalism.com/2019/08/12/wonder-woman-1984-re-shooting-wrapped-a-must-read-guide-for-fans/ |title=Wonder Woman 1984: Re-shooting wrapped? A Must Read Guide for Fans!!! |date=August 12, 2019|access-date=February 1, 2020 |website=UnionJournalism.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Post-production ===\n[[Richard Pearson (film editor)|Richard Pearson]] will serve as the editor for ''Wonder Woman 1984''.<ref name=\"Production\"/> John Moffatt (''[[Harry Potter (film series)|Harry Potter]]'' and ''[[Life (2017 film)|Life]]'') will serve as the overall visual effects supervisor for the film.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Marc |first1=Christopher |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' Adds ''Harry Potter and The Deathly Hallows'' VFX Supervisor |url=https://hnentertainment.co/wonder-woman-1984-adds-harry-potter-and-the-deathly-hallows-vfx-supervisor/ |access-date=November 28, 2018 |work=HNEntertainment.co |date=November 28, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129012720/https://hnentertainment.co/wonder-woman-1984-adds-harry-potter-and-the-deathly-hallows-vfx-supervisor/ |archive-date=November 29, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Frei |first1=Vincent |url=https://www.artofvfx.com/wonder-woman-1984/ |title= Wonder Woman 1984/ |work=Art of VFX |date=December 8, 2019|accessdate=December 8, 2019}}</ref> Double Negative ([[DNEG]]), [[Framestore]] and [[Method Studios]] will provide the visual effects for the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dneg.com/show/wonder-woman-1984/ |title=Wonder Woman 1984 |accessdate=January 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102002204/https://www.dneg.com/show/wonder-woman-1984/|archive-date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.framestore.com/work/upcoming-film-releases |title=Framestore upcoming film releases |accessdate=February 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170920092547/https://framestore.com/work/upcoming-film-releases|archive-date=September 20, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.methodstudios.com/en/in-production/ |title=Method Studios Features & Episodics In Production |accessdate=May 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190511141707/https://www.methodstudios.com/en/in-production/|archive-date=May 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Alexis Wajsbrot]] is serving as the visual effects supervisor for Framestore.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Frei |first1=Vincent |url=https://www.artofvfx.com/spider-man-far-from-home-alexis-wajsbrot-vfx-supervisor-framestore/ |title=Spider-man \u2013 Far From Home: Alexis Wasjbrot \u2013 VFX Supervisor \u2013 Framestore |work=Art of VFX |date=July 16, 2019|accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> In December 2019, Jenkins revealed work on the film was completed five months in advance of the original release date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487309/wonder-woman-1984-is-technically-done-and-heres-the-first-cuts-runtime|title=Wonder Woman 1984 Is 'Technically Done' And Here's The First Cut's Runtime|date=December 21, 2019|website=CINEMABLEND}}</ref>\n\n== Music ==\nOn August 22, 2018, [[Hans Zimmer]] was announced as the composer for ''Wonder Woman 1984'', replacing [[Rupert Gregson-Williams]] who scored the first film. Zimmer previously scored ''[[Man of Steel (film)|Man of Steel]]'' and ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'', the first and second films in the [[DC Extended Universe]].<ref name=\"Zimmer\">{{cite web |title=Hans Zimmer to Score Patty Jenkins' ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/22/hans-zimmer-to-score-patty-jenkins-wonder-woman-1984/ |work=Film Music Reporter|access-date=August 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181002023825/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/22/hans-zimmer-to-score-patty-jenkins-wonder-woman-1984/|archive-date=October 2, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''Wonder Woman 1984'' is scheduled to be released by Warner Bros. Pictures in the United States in RealD 3D, Dolby Cinema, and IMAX 3D{{citation needed|date=March 2020}} on August 14, 2020.<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date August\"/> It was originally announced for December 13, 2019,<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date December\">{{cite web |last1=Galuppo |first1=Mia |last2=Shanley |first2=Patrick |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Sets Release Date |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-2-release-date-set-1022782 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=July 26, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170726024056/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-2-release-date-set-1022782 |archivedate=July 26, 2017}}</ref> and then moved to November 1, 2019,<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date November\">{{cite web |last1=McClintock |first1=Pamela |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Release Date Moved Up 6 Weeks |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-2-release-date-moves-up-6-weeks-1057572 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=June 16, 2018 |date=November 13, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616153408/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-2-release-date-moves-up-6-weeks-1057572 |archive-date=June 16, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> then to June 5, 2020.<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date June\">{{cite news |first1=Anthony |last1=D'Alessandro |accessdate=October 22, 2018 |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' Flies To Summer 2020 |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/wonder-woman-1984-flies-to-summer-2020-1202487260/ |newspaper=Deadline |date=October 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181022213802/https://deadline.com/2018/10/wonder-woman-1984-flies-to-summer-2020-1202487260/|archive-date=October 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On March 24, 2020, the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] led to the film [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema|being delayed]] until August 14, 2020.<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date August\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-1984-release-pushed-coronavirus-concerns-1284285|title='Wonder Woman 1984' Release Pushed to Late Summer Amid Coronavirus Pandemic|first1=Mia|last1=Galuppo|first2=Pamela|last2=McClintock|date=March 24, 2020|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324190613/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-1984-release-pushed-coronavirus-concerns-1284285|archive-date=March 24, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nLike its predecessor, ''Wonder Woman 1984'' will not be shown in several Arab and Muslim nations due to Gadot's past as an [[Israel Defense Forces|Israeli soldier]] and the enforcement of the [[Arab League boycott of Israel|Israeli boycott]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stepfeed.com/egyptian-actor-criticized-for-taking-acting-role-with-israel-s-gal-gadot-4487|title=Egyptian actor criticized for taking 'acting role' with Israel's Gal Gadot|first=Rayana|last=Khalaf|date=November 19, 2019|website=StepFeed}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing==\n[[File:Patty Jenkins, Chris Pine & Gal Gadot at the 2018 Comic-Con International 3.jpg|thumb|[[Patty Jenkins]], [[Chris Pine]], and [[Gal Gadot]] promoting ''Wonder Woman 1984'' at the 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]]]\n\nOn June 22, 2018, it was reported that Gal Gadot would be attending Warner Bros.' DC presentation at the 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con]] (SDCC), and some footage from the film would be shown to promote it.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/wonder-woman-comic-con-surprise-gal-gadot-footage-warner-bros-aquaman-1202414752/ |title=Gal Gadot and ''Wonder Woman 1984'' Planned As Warner's Big Comic-Con Surprise |first1=Anthony |last1=D'Alessandro |first2=Dominic |last2=Patten |date=June 21, 2018 |work=Deadline|access-date=June 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622193041/https://deadline.com/2018/06/wonder-woman-comic-con-surprise-gal-gadot-footage-warner-bros-aquaman-1202414752/|archive-date=June 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Director [[Patty Jenkins]] and actors Gadot and [[Chris Pine]] attended the ''Wonder Woman 1984'' panel at SDCC on July 21, 2018, where a short clip of the film was shown.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/wonder-woman-1984-patty-jenkins-gal-gadot-chris-pine-comic-con-1202880369/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' Team Talks '80s Setting, Chris Pine's Resurrection |first1=Erin |last=Nyren |date=July 21, 2018 |work=Variety|access-date=August 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828170110/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/wonder-woman-1984-patty-jenkins-gal-gadot-chris-pine-comic-con-1202880369/|archive-date=August 28, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> New footage was shown during [[ShoWest Convention|CinemaCon]] 2019 in Las Vegas, Nevada, with a first look at Kristen Wiig in the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/04/03/wonder-woman-1984-footage-shown-at-cinemacon-includes-first-look-at-kristen-wiig-cheetah |title=Wonder Woman 1984 Footage Shown at CinemaCon Includes First Look at Kristen Wiig |first1=Jim |last=Vejvoda|date=April 4, 2019 |work=IGN|access-date=October 27, 2019}}</ref> In June 2019, Warner Bros. screened an extended look to European exhibitors at [[CineEurope]] in Barcelona, Spain.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/warner-bros-previews-joker-wonder-woman-1984-birds-prey-1218951 |title=CineEurope: Warner Bros. Offers Glimpses of 'Joker', 'Wonder Woman 1984', 'Godzilla vs. Kong' and 'Birds of Prey'|first1=Jennifer |last=Green |date=June 17, 2019 |work=TheHollywoodReporter |access-date=November 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA teaser poster debuted on June 5, 2019, one year ahead of the film's release date.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/06/05/patty-jenkin-and-gal-gadot-debut-first-poster-for-wonder-woman-1984/#56ad482b38dc |title=Gal Gadot And Patty Jenkins Debut First Poster For ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |first1=Scott |last=Mendelson |date=June 5, 2019 |work=Forbes|access-date=June 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606161401/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/06/05/patty-jenkin-and-gal-gadot-debut-first-poster-for-wonder-woman-1984/#56ad482b38dc|archive-date=June 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2019, it was announced that the film's first trailer would debut during [[Comic Con Experience]] CCXP 2019 on December 8, with Gal Gadot and director Patty Jenkins attending the event in S\u00e3o Paulo, Brazil.<ref name=\"WW84-CCXP\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20191021005733/en/Gal-Gadot-Director-Patty-Jenkins-Set-Give |title='Gal Gadot & Director Patty Jenkins Set to Give CCXP Brazil Attendees an Unforgettable Finale With a Special Showcase for Wonder Woman 1984 That Will Close the Con With a Bang and Kick Off the Countdown to the Film\u2019s 2020 Release |date=October 21, 2019 |work=BusinessWire|access-date=October 21, 2019}}</ref> By the end of the month, [[WarnerMedia]] Entertainment debuted new footage from the film during the [[HBO Max]] presentation to the press.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/10/30/wonder-woman-1984-white-house-fight-footage-scene |title=Wonder Woman 1984: New Footage Shows Diana Fighting Inside the White House |first1=Jesse |last1=Schedeen|date=October 30, 2019 |work=IGN |access-date=October 31, 2019}}</ref> The first trailer debuted on December 8 at the 2019 Comic Con Experience (CCXP), with the show being livestreamed on Twitter around the world in real time.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/wonder-woman-1984-trailer-gal-gadot-kristen-wiig-1203427630/ |title=\"'Wonder Woman 1984' Trailer: Gal Gadot Returns With Pedro Pascal, Kristen Wiig |first1=Lorraine |last1=Wheat|date=December 8, 2019 |work=Variety |access-date=December 8, 2019}}</ref> Trailer music theme is Sebastian B\u00f6hm's instrumental remix of \"[[Blue Monday (New Order song)|Blue Monday]]\" by [[New Order (band)|New Order]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sfM7_JLk-84|title=Wonder Woman 1984 \u2013 Official Trailer}}</ref> The same day, [[Film poster#Character posters|character posters]] for Wonder Woman, [[Maxwell Lord]], [[Cheetah (comics)#Barbara Ann Minerva|Barbara Ann Minerva]] and [[Steve Trevor]] were released.<ref>{{cite news |last1= Adler |first1= Matthew |title= Wonder Woman 1984 Character Posters Reveal First Look at Kristen Wiig as Cheetah |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/08/wonder-woman-1984-first-look-kristen-wiig-cheetah-revealed-poster |accessdate=December 9, 2019 |work= IGN|date=December 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Future==\n===Sequel===\nIn January 2019, after principal photography on ''Wonder Woman 1984'' was completed, director and co-writer Patty Jenkins announced that the plot for a third ''Wonder Woman'' film is currently mapped out.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/01/patty-jenkins-interview-i-am-the-night-wonder-woman |title=''Wonder Woman'' Director Patty Jenkins on Her New TV Drama I Am the Night |first=Joy |last=Press |website=HWD |accessdate=January 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190127150040/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/01/patty-jenkins-interview-i-am-the-night-wonder-woman|archive-date=January 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The filmmaker stated that the plot of the next installment would take place during the modern day.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-3-will-not-be-set-past-says-director-patty-jenkins-1179511 |title=Director Patty Jenkins: ''Wonder Woman 3'' Will Be a 'Contemporary Story' |first=Aaron |last=Couch |date=January 26, 2019 |website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=January 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128135222/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-3-will-not-be-set-past-says-director-patty-jenkins-1179511|archive-date=January 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> By December 2019, Jenkins expressed that the wait between the second and third films will be longer than the time it took to release the first sequel.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://heroichollywood.com/patty-jenkins-gal-gadot-wonder-woman-3-plans/ |title=Patty Jenkins Already Has The Story Planned For Gal Gadot\u2019s \u2018Wonder Woman 3\u2019 |first= Sebastian |last= Peris |date=December 9, 2019 |website=Heroic Hollywood|access-date=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Spin-off===\nIn December 2019, director Patty Jenkins announced that a ''Wonder Woman'' spin-off film is in development, with the story focusing on the [[Amazons (DC Comics)|Amazons]] of [[Themyscira (DC Comics)|Themyscira]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-director-patty-jenkins-considering-amazon-spinoff-1260683|title= 'Wonder Woman' Director Patty Jenkins Considering Amazon Spinoff |website=The Hollywood Reporter| last= McMillan | first=Graeme |date=December 9, 2019| accessdate=December 9, 2019}}</ref> Jenkins is attached as executive producer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newsarama.com/48175-jenkins-developing-wonder-woman-spin-off-for-the-amazons-report.html |title=Jenkins Developing Wonder Woman Spin-Off for the Amazons - Report |last=Arrant |first=Chris |website=[[Newsarama]] |date=December 9, 2019 |access-date=December 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q33408623|c=Category:Wonder Woman 1984|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|s=no|q=no|species=no|wikt=no|display=''Wonder Woman 1984''}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title}}\n* {{Mojo title}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes}}\n* {{Metacritic film}}\n\n{{Wonder Woman}}\n{{Wonder Woman in popular media}}\n{{DC Extended Universe}}\n{{DC Comics films}}\n{{Patty Jenkins}}\n{{Portal bar|Film|United States|Speculative fiction}}\n\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020s action films]]\n[[Category:2020s feminist films]]\n[[Category:2020s sequel films]]\n[[Category:2020s superhero films]]\n[[Category:2020s fantasy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:American superhero films]]\n[[Category:Atlas Entertainment films]]\n[[Category:Cold War films]]\n[[Category:DC Extended Universe films]]\n[[Category:Films based on Greco-Roman mythology]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Patty Jenkins]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Zack Snyder]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1984]]\n[[Category:Films set in London]]\n[[Category:Films set in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Films set in the White House]]\n[[Category:Films shot in the Canary Islands]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hertfordshire]]\n[[Category:Films shot in London]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Spain]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Virginia]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:IMAX films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Patty Jenkins]]\n[[Category:Superheroine films]]\n[[Category:Superhero films featuring female antagonists]]\n[[Category:Upcoming IMAX films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming sequel films]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. films]]\n[[Category:Wonder Woman films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Upcoming American superhero film}}\n{{Use American English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Wonder Woman 1984\n| image          = Wonder Woman 1984 poster.jpg\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Teaser poster\n| director       = [[Patty Jenkins]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Charles Roven]]\n* [[Deborah Snyder]]\n* [[Zack Snyder]]\n* Patty Jenkins\n* [[Gal Gadot]]\n* Stephen Jones\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* Patty Jenkins\n* [[Geoff Johns]]\n* [[David Callaham]]\n}}\n| story          = {{Plainlist|\n* Patty Jenkins\n* Geoff Johns\n}}\n| based_on       = {{Based on|[[Wonder Woman]]|[[William Moulton Marston]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://findawriter.wgaeast.org/project/1152284/wonder-woman-1984 |title=Wonder Woman 1984 \n|website=findawriter.wgaeast.org |accessdate=February 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Gal Gadot<!--PER CREDITS BILLING ORDER-->\n* [[Chris Pine]]\n* [[Kristen Wiig]]\n* [[Pedro Pascal]]\n* [[Robin Wright]]\n* [[Connie Nielsen]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Hans Zimmer]]\n| cinematography = [[Matthew Jensen (cinematographer)|Matthew Jensen]]\n| editing        = [[Richard Pearson (film editor)|Richard Pearson]]\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[DC Films]]\n* [[Atlas Entertainment]]\n* [[The Stone Quarry]]\n* [[Mad Ghost Productions]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.madghostproductions.com/category/film/ |title=Film \u2013 Mad Ghost Productions \n|website=www.madghostproductions.com |accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614005756/http://www.madghostproductions.com/category/film/|archive-date=June 14, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Warner Bros. Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|8|14|United States}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $175 million<ref name=WrapStream>{{cite web |url= https://www.thewrap.com/wonder-woman-1984-streaming-no-theater-warner-bros/ |title= Warner Bros Debates Whether \u2018Wonder Woman 1984\u2019 Should Skip Theaters for Streaming (Exclusive)|website=[[TheWrap]] |date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Wonder Woman 1984''''' (also marketed as '''''WW84: Wonder Woman 1984''''') is an upcoming American [[superhero film]] based on the [[DC Comics]] character [[Wonder Woman]]. It is the sequel to 2017's ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'' and the ninth installment in the [[DC Extended Universe]] (DCEU). The film is directed by [[Patty Jenkins]] from a script she wrote with [[Geoff Johns]] and [[David Callaham]], and a story by Johns and Jenkins, and stars [[Gal Gadot]] as Diana Prince/Wonder Woman, alongside [[Chris Pine]], [[Kristen Wiig]], [[Pedro Pascal]], [[Robin Wright]], and [[Connie Nielsen]] in supporting roles. Set in 1984, the film follows Diana as she faces off against [[Maxwell Lord]] and [[Cheetah (comics)|Cheetah]].\n\nDiscussion of a sequel began shortly after the release of the first film in June 2017, and the decision to proceed was confirmed the following month. Principal photography began on June 13, 2018\u2014with filming taking place at [[Warner Bros. Studios, Leavesden]] in England, as well as the District of Columbia and Northern Virginia in the United States, London and Duxford in England, Tenerife and Fuerteventura in the Canary Islands, and Almer\u00eda in Andalusia, Spain\u2014and wrapped on December 22, 2018, after a six-month shoot. Additional filming took place in July 2019.\n\n''Wonder Woman 1984'' is scheduled to be released in the United States by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] in [[RealD 3D]], [[Dolby Cinema]], [[IMAX]], and [[IMAX 3D]] on August 14, 2020.\n\n==Premise==\nIn 1984, [[Wonder Woman|Diana Prince]] comes into conflict with two formidable foes - media businessman [[Maxwell Lord]] and friend-turned-enemy [[Cheetah (comics)|Barbara Ann Minerva/Cheetah]] - while reuniting with her lover, [[Steve Trevor]].<ref name=\"ColdWar\">{{cite web |url=https://amp.pastemagazine.com/articles/2017/07/wonder-woman-2-may-be-set-during-the-cold-war-and.html |title=Report: Wonder Woman 2 Set During the Cold War, Chris Pine to Return |website=amp.pastemagazine |date=July 11, 2017|access-date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626101027/https://amp.pastemagazine.com/articles/2017/07/wonder-woman-2-may-be-set-during-the-cold-war-and.html|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Cheetah confirmation\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Gal Gadot]] as [[Wonder Woman|Diana Prince/Wonder Woman]]: An immortal [[Demigod|demigoddess]], [[Amazons (DC Comics)|Amazon]] princess and warrior. Diana is the daughter of [[Hippolyta (DC Comics)|Hippolyta]], the Amazonian queen of [[Themyscira (DC Comics)|Themyscira]] and [[Zeus (DC Comics)|Zeus]], the king of the [[Olympian Gods (DC Comics)|Olympian Gods]].<ref name=\"Sequel-RT\"/>\n*[[Chris Pine]] as [[Steve Trevor]]: An American pilot and the love interest of Diana, who had presumably died during the events of [[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|the first film]].<ref name=\"WW84Title\">{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/06/wonder-woman-1984-first-look-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-chris-pine-1201974200/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' First Look: Gal Gadot and Patty Jenkins Reunite, While Chris Pine Makes Surprise Return |last=Sharf |first=Zack |publisher=[[IndieWire]] |date=June 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 13, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620123231/http://www.indiewire.com/2018/06/wonder-woman-1984-first-look-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-chris-pine-1201974200/ |archive-date=June 20, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Kristen Wiig]] as [[Cheetah (comics)|Barbara Ann Minerva/Cheetah]]: An [[Archaeology|archaeologist]] who befriends Diana before becoming imbued with a [[Cheetah|cheetah]]-like appearance and abilities.<ref name=\"WiigCast\"/><ref name=\"Cheetah confirmation\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Newby |first1=Richard |title=The Bad Guys Are Inheriting the DC Universe |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dc-movie-universe-is-going-villains-1118179 |accessdate=June 11, 2018 |date=June 8, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612145329/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dc-movie-universe-is-going-villains-1118179 |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Pedro Pascal]] as [[Maxwell Lord|Maxwell \"Max\" Lord]]: A media businessman and entrepreneur who is famous for TV [[Infomercial|infomercials]].<ref name=\"PascalCast\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Pantozzi |first1=Jill |title=Pedro Pascal's Wonder Woman 1984 Character Is Exactly Who You Thought He Was |url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/pedro-pascals-wonder-woman-1984-character-is-exactly-wh-1839321290 |accessdate=October 24, 2019 |work=Gizmodo |date=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Robin Wright]] as [[Antiope (comics)|Antiope]]: Hippolyta's deceased sister, general of the Amazon army and Diana's aunt.<ref name=\"NielsenWright\"/>\n*[[Connie Nielsen]] as [[Hippolyta (DC Comics)|Hippolyta]]: The queen of [[Themyscira (DC Comics)|Themyscira]] and Diana's mother.<ref name=\"NielsenWright\"/>\n\nAdditionally, [[Natasha Rothwell]], [[Ravi Patel (actor)|Ravi Patel]], [[Gabriella Wilde]], [[Kristoffer Polaha]] and [[Amr Waked]] have been cast in undisclosed roles.<ref name=\"Rothwell\">{{cite news |last1=Galuppo |first1=Mia |title=''Insecure'' Star Natasha Rothwell Joins ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/natasha-rothwell-joins-wonder-woman-1984-1129667 |accessdate=July 29, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=July 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725044002/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/natasha-rothwell-joins-wonder-woman-1984-1129667|archive-date=July 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"PatelWilde\">{{cite news |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=Ravi Patel & Gabriella Wilde Boarding ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/wonder-woman-1984-casting-ravi-patel-1202435167/ |accessdate=July 29, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=July 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729085835/https://deadline.com/2018/07/wonder-woman-1984-casting-ravi-patel-1202435167/|archive-date=July 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Polaha\">{{cite news |last1=Polaha |first1=Kristoffer |title=Why I Love Doing Hallmark Movies, an Actor's Confession (Guest Column) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/why-i-love-doing-hallmark-movies-an-actors-confession-guest-column-1163165 |accessdate=November 21, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=November 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181121194830/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/why-i-love-doing-hallmark-movies-an-actors-confession-guest-column-1163165|archive-date=November 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/amrwaked/status/1195801138928504837|title=\u0627\u0646\u062a\u0638\u0631\u0648\u0627 \u0638\u0647\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0641\u064a \u0641\u064a\u0644\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u0623\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u0627\u0631\u0642\u0629 \u0661\u0669\u0668\u0664 (\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0632\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u062b\u0627\u0646\u064a) \u0625\u062e\u0631\u0627\u062c \u0628\u0627\u062a\u064a \u062c\u064a\u0646\u0643\u064a\u0646\u0632 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u062a\u0648\u0642\u0639 \u0646\u0632\u0648\u0644\u0647 \u0641\u064a \u064a\u0648\u0646\u064a\u0648 \u0662\u0660\u0662\u0660. \u064a\u0627 \u0631\u0628 \u064a\u0639\u062c\u0628\u0643\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u064a\u0644\u0645.|first=Amr|last=Waked|date=November 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n[[Gal Gadot]], who originally signed for three feature films with ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'' being her second, had extended her contract beyond that.<ref name=\"Sequel-RT\">{{cite web |last1=Schmitz |first1=Greg Dean |title=''Wonder Woman'' Sequel Details Emerge, And More Movie News |url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/article/wonder-woman-sequel-details-emerge-and-more-movie-news/ |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |date=June 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170724160242/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2017/07/24/wonder-woman-sequel-title-revealed.html|archive-date=July 24, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The director of the first film, [[Patty Jenkins]], who initially signed for only one film, had expressed interest in returning to direct the sequel.<ref name=\"SignedOnlyOne\">{{cite web |last1=Kit |first1=Bory |title=''Wonder Woman'' Director Patty Jenkins Not Signed for Sequel |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-director-patty-jenkins-not-signed-sequel-1010845 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |date=June 7, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611065039/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-director-patty-jenkins-not-signed-sequel-1010845|archive-date=June 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"ToAmerica\">{{cite web |last1=Goldberg |first1=Matt |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Setting Will Take Diana To America |url=https://collider.com/wonder-woman-2-setting/ |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |date=June 5, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170605201447/http://collider.com/wonder-woman-2-setting/|archive-date=June 5, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2017, during an interview with ''Variety'', comic book writer [[Geoff Johns]] revealed that he and Jenkins had started writing the treatment for a ''Wonder Woman'' sequel and that he had a \"cool idea for the second one\".<ref name=\"GeoffJohnsAboutSequel\">{{cite news |last1=Lang |first1=Brent |title=DC Film's Jon Berg, Geoff Johns on Success of ''Wonder Woman'' and Sequel Plans (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/jon-berg-geoff-johns-wonder-woman-sequel-justice-league-1202471557/ |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |work=Variety |date=June 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701022527/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/jon-berg-geoff-johns-wonder-woman-sequel-justice-league-1202471557/|archive-date=July 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"JenkinsWriting\">{{cite news |last1=Nyren |first1=Erin |title=Patty Jenkins Developing ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/wonder-woman-sequel-patty-jenkins-1202472855/ |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |work=Variety |date=June 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170620221847/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/wonder-woman-sequel-patty-jenkins-1202472855/|archive-date=June 20, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> While speaking in a Q&A at a Women in Film screening of the film, Jenkins confirmed she would indeed direct the sequel.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sobel |first1=Ariel |title=BREAKING: Patty Jenkins Confirms She's Directing the ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel |url=https://www.advocate.com/film/2017/6/29/breaking-patty-jenkins-confirms-shes-directing-wonder-woman-sequel |website=Advocate |accessdate=June 30, 2017 |date=June 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630072821/https://www.advocate.com/film/2017/6/29/breaking-patty-jenkins-confirms-shes-directing-wonder-woman-sequel|archive-date=June 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> However, Jenkins later tweeted that \"it wasn't a confirmation. Just talking about ideas and hopes\".<ref name=\"JenkinsBacktracks\">{{cite news |last1=Wood |first1=Matt |title=Patty Jenkins Backtracks Her ''Wonder Woman 2'' Confirmation |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1676140/patty-jenkins-backtracks-wonder-woman-2-confirmation |accessdate=July 23, 2017 |work=CinemaBlend |date=June 30, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804121758/http://www.cinemablend.com/news/1676140/patty-jenkins-backtracks-wonder-woman-2-confirmation|archive-date=August 4, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn July 22, 2017, at [[San Diego Comic-Con]], the studio officially announced a sequel would be produced, with Jenkins returning as director; its title was listed as ''Wonder Woman 2''.<ref name=\"OfficiallyAnnouncedCC\">{{cite news |last1=Freeman |first1=Molly |title=Warner Bros. Officially Announces ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel |url=https://screenrant.com/wonder-woman-2-sequel-confirmed-warner-bros/ |accessdate=July 23, 2017 |work=Screen Rant |date=July 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723065320/http://screenrant.com/wonder-woman-2-sequel-confirmed-warner-bros/|archive-date=July 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"TitleComicCon\">{{cite news |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=Warner Bros Confirms DC Universe Pic Titles: ''Wonder Woman II'', ''Flashpoint'' & More \u2013 Comic-Con |url=https://deadline.com/2017/07/wonder-woman-ii-flashpoint-1202133919/ |accessdate=July 23, 2017 |work=Deadline |date=July 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722235732/http://deadline.com/2017/07/wonder-woman-ii-flashpoint-1202133919/|archive-date=July 22, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In September 2017, it was officially confirmed that Jenkins would be directing the sequel.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sharf |first1=Zack |title=''Wonder Woman 2'': Patty Jenkins Signing Historic Deal to Become Highest Paid Female Director in Hollywood |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/wonder-woman-2-patty-jenkins-director-highest-paid-female-1201867661/ |accessdate=September 11, 2017 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=September 11, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911073253/http://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/wonder-woman-2-patty-jenkins-director-highest-paid-female-1201867661/|archive-date=September 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On September 13, 2017, it was reported that ''[[The Expendables (2010 film)|The Expendables]]'' writer [[David Callaham]] would join the film to co-write the script with Jenkins and Johns, who were already working on it for several months.<ref name=\"CallahamWriting\">{{cite news |last1=Kit |first1=Borys |title=''The Expendables'' Writer Joins Patty Jenkins, Geoff Johns to Write ''Wonder Woman 2'' (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/expendables-writer-dave-callaham-joins-wonder-woman-2-writing-team-1038759 |accessdate=September 20, 2017 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=September 13, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170919042419/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/expendables-writer-dave-callaham-joins-wonder-woman-2-writing-team-1038759|archive-date=September 19, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\nOn February 28, 2018, it was reported that the film would be shot with [[IMAX]] film cameras in select action sequences.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/money/news/imax-imax-q4-2017-results-earnings-call-transcript/ar-BBJGs2A |title=IMAX (IMAX) Q4 2017 Results \u2013 Earnings Call Transcript |date=February 28, 2018 |accessdate=June 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614095003/https://www.msn.com/en-us/money/news/imax-imax-q4-2017-results-earnings-call-transcript/ar-BBJGs2A|archive-date=June 14, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> By late May 2018, long-time DCEU producer [[Zack Snyder]] confirmed on social media platform [[Vero (app)|Vero]] that he, along with his wife [[Deborah Snyder]], would serve as producers on the ''Wonder Woman'' sequel.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/updates-on-incredibles-2-supergirl-the-expanse-and-m-1826469809 |title=Updates On ''Incredibles 2'', ''Supergirl'', ''The Expanse'', and More |last=Whitbrook |first=James |work=io9 |access-date=June 6, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180605152007/https://io9.gizmodo.com/updates-on-incredibles-2-supergirl-the-expanse-and-m-1826469809 |archive-date=June 5, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> On June 13, 2018, the title of the film was announced to be ''Wonder Woman 1984''.<ref name=\"WW84Title\"/> A source close to Jenkins described it as a stand-alone film \"in the same way that ''[[Indiana Jones (franchise)|Indiana Jones]]'' or ''[[Production of the James Bond films|[James] Bond]]'' films are, instead of one continuous story that requires many installments.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/03/wonder-woman-1984-not-a-sequel-1202051300/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' Is 'Not a Sequel' |last=Nordine |first=Michael |date=March 15, 2019 |website=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=March 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Pre-production===\nPre-production officially began by early December 2017 in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web |last=Nambiar |first=Smitha |url=http://pursuenews.com/director-patty-jenkins-confirms-wonder-woman-2-pre-production/ |date=December 6, 2017|access-date=December 6, 2017 |title=Director Patty Jenkins Confirms ''Wonder Woman 2'' Is in Pre-Production |website=PursueNews.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210195120/http://pursuenews.com/director-patty-jenkins-confirms-wonder-woman-2-pre-production|archive-date=December 10, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> That same month, director Patty Jenkins stated that the film would be another great love story.<ref>{{cite web |last=Daly |first=Rhian |url=https://www.nme.com/news/film/director-patty-jenkins-teases-details-wonder-woman-2-storyline-2167289/ |date=December 1, 2017 |accessdate=December 1, 2017 |title=Director Patty Jenkins teases more details of ''Wonder Woman 2'' storyline |website=[[NME]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201221520/http://www.nme.com/news/film/director-patty-jenkins-teases-details-wonder-woman-2-storyline-2167289|archive-date=December 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2018, the film was confirmed to be set in the 1980s.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/wonder-woman-2-setting-patty-jenkins/ |title=Patty Jenkins Confirms ''Wonder Woman 2'' Is Set in The '80s |last=Stauffer |first=Derek |date=April 24, 2018 |publisher=ScreenRant |accessdate=April 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180425163050/https://screenrant.com/wonder-woman-2-setting-patty-jenkins/|archive-date=April 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The next month, production designer [[Aline Bonetto]] (''[[Am\u00e9lie]]'', ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'') was announced to be returning for the sequel, as well as [[Academy Award]] winner [[Lindy Hemming]], also returning as costume designer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://omegaunderground.com/2018/05/21/production-designer-aline-bonetto-returns-for-woman-woman-2/ |title=Production Designer Aline Bonetto Returns For ''Woman Woman 2'' |last=Williams |first=Caleb |date=May 21, 2018 |publisher=OmegaGround |accessdate=May 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613184634/https://omegaunderground.com/2018/05/21/production-designer-aline-bonetto-returns-for-woman-woman-2/|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn September 2017, Gal Gadot was confirmed to return as the title character.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=Patty Jenkins Closes Deal to Direct ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/patty-jenkins-wonder-woman-sequel-director-1202548413/ |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=May 29, 2018 |date=September 11, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911215145/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/patty-jenkins-wonder-woman-sequel-director-1202548413/ |archive-date=September 11, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> On February 28, 2018, it was reported that [[Kristen Wiig]] was in talks with the studio to play [[Cheetah (comics)|Cheetah]], the main villain of the film,<ref name=\"WiigCast\">{{cite news |last1=Jr |first1=Mike Fleming |title=Kristen Wiig Being Lassoed For Villain Role On ''Wonder Woman 2'' |url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/kristen-wiig-wonder-woman-2-cheetah-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-villain2-1202306419/ |accessdate=March 2, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=February 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310040404/https://deadline.com/2018/02/kristen-wiig-wonder-woman-2-cheetah-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-villain2-1202306419/|archive-date=March 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> with director Patty Jenkins confirming her casting the next month.<ref name=\"Cheetah confirmation\">{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2018/03/09/kristen-wiig-will-star-in-wonder-woman-sequel-as-the-cheetah-patty-jenkins-confirms/ |title=Kristen Wiig will star in ''Wonder Woman'' sequel as the Cheetah, Patty Jenkins confirms |date=March 9, 2018 |first=David |last=Betancourt |work=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=June 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310135642/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2018/03/09/kristen-wiig-will-star-in-wonder-woman-sequel-as-the-cheetah-patty-jenkins-confirms/|archive-date=March 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> By March 28, [[Pedro Pascal]], who played [[Ed Indelicato]] in the pilot of the canceled [[Wonder Woman (2011 TV pilot)|2011 ''Wonder Woman'' television adaptation]], was cast in an undisclosed key role, later revealed to be [[Maxwell Lord]].<ref name=\"PascalCast\">{{cite news |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=''Narcos'' Star Pedro Pascal Lands Key Role in ''Wonder Woman'' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/ |accessdate=May 29, 2018 |work=Variety |date=March 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180329010138/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/|archive-date=March 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=McMillan |first1=Graeme |title='Wonder Woman 1984': Who Is Maxwell Lord? |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-1984-who-is-pedro-pascals-maxwell-lord-1249865 |accessdate=October 26, 2019 |work=TheHollywoodReporter |date=October 24, 2019}}</ref> On June 13, Jenkins confirmed the return of [[Chris Pine]] as Steve Trevor via [[Twitter]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://twitter.com/PattyJenks/status/1006884175532740608 |title=Patty Jenkins on Twitter |work=Twitter|access-date=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617152137/https://twitter.com/pattyjenks/status/1006884175532740608|archive-date=June 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On July 24, 2018, Natasha Rothwell was announced to be cast in an undisclosed role.<ref name=\"Rothwell\"/> A few days later, on July 27, [[Ravi Patel (actor)|Ravi Patel]] and [[Gabriella Wilde]] also joined the film, with their roles being kept under wraps as well.<ref name=\"PatelWilde\"/> By late August, [[Connie Nielsen]] and [[Robin Wright]] were confirmed to reprise their roles as [[Hippolyta (DC Comics)|Hippolyta]] and [[Antiope (comics)|Antiope]] in a flashback sequence.<ref name=\"NielsenWright\">{{cite news |title=The Good Fight with Robin Wright |url=https://www.net-a-porter.com/us/en/porter/article-b36c5430c852c9af |accessdate=September 1, 2018 |work=Net-A-Porter |date=August 31, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831232242/https://www.net-a-porter.com/us/en/porter/article-b36c5430c852c9af|archive-date=August 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2018, [[Kristoffer Polaha]] revealed that he has a role in the film.<ref name=\"Polaha\"/>\n\n===Filming===\nPrincipal photography began on June 13, 2018, under the working title ''Magic Hour''.<ref name=\"Production\">{{cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180613005640/en/Cameras-Roll-Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-%E2%80%9CWonder-Woman |title=Cameras Roll on Warner Bros. Pictures' ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |work=Business Wire |date=June 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613234147/https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180613005640/en/Cameras-Roll-Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-%E2%80%9CWonder-Woman|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Filming took place at Warner Bros. Studios, Leavesden in England, and at a number of locations around the District of Columbia and Northern Virginia in the United States, including the [[Landmark Mall]] in Alexandria, Virginia and Georgetown during June and July 2018,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bizjournals.com/washington/news/2018/05/03/wonder-woman-2-to-film-at-alexandrias-deadlandmark.html |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' to film at Alexandria's dead Landmark Mall |last=Neibauer |first=Michael |date=May 3, 2018 |publisher=Washington Business Journal |accessdate=May 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-2-shooting-stateside-summer/ |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Reportedly Shooting Stateside This Summer |last=Villaverde |first=Noah |date=March 18, 2018 |website=Heroichollywood.com |accessdate=March 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320111741/https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-2-shooting-stateside-summer/|archive-date=March 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://georgetownmetropolitan.com/2018/05/24/wonder-woman-2-to-film-in-georgetown/ |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' to Film in Georgetown |date=May 24, 2018 |publisher=The Georgetown Metropolitan |accessdate=June 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143852/https://georgetownmetropolitan.com/2018/05/24/wonder-woman-2-to-film-in-georgetown/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> with scenes shot in Alexandria from June 18 through July 14.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/wonder-woman-2-starring-gal-gadot-open-casting-call/ |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Starring Gal Gadot Open Casting Call |date=June 14, 2018 |website=ProjectCasting.com |accessdate=June 16, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616130440/http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/wonder-woman-2-starring-gal-gadot-open-casting-call/|archive-date=June 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Filming occurred outside the U.S. Capitol in Washington, D.C., during mid-June.{{cn|date=February 2020}} Other filming locations around D.C. included the [[Penn Quarter]] neighborhood, [[McPherson Square]], the [[DAR Constitution Hall]] near the [[White House]], the [[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]] ([[Smithsonian Institution|Smithsonian]]), and the [[Lincoln Memorial]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fox5dc.com/news/local-news/-wonder-woman-continues-to-impact-traffic-around-dc-road-closures-in-penn-quarter |title=''Wonder Woman'' continues to impact traffic around DC, road closures in Penn Quarter |date=June 17, 2018 |website=Fox5dc.com |access-date=July 7, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707202222/http://www.fox5dc.com/news/local-news/-wonder-woman-continues-to-impact-traffic-around-dc-road-closures-in-penn-quarter |archive-date=July 7, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fox5dc.com/news/local-news/filming-for-rumored-wonder-woman-sequel-shutting-down-several-streets-around-mcpherson-square |title=Filming shutting down several streets around McPherson Square this weekend |date=July 6, 2018 |website=Fox5dc.com |accessdate=July 7, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707171636/http://www.fox5dc.com/news/local-news/filming-for-rumored-wonder-woman-sequel-shutting-down-several-streets-around-mcpherson-square|archive-date=July 7, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/fantasy-and-reality-clash-as-movie-makers-film-wonder-woman-in-dc/2018/07/07/4f044522-8215-11e8-b9a5-7e1c013f8c33_story.html |title=Fantasy and reality clash as movie makers film ''Wonder Woman'' in D.C. |last=Ruane |first=Michael E. |date=July 7, 2018 |publisher=The Washington Post|access-date=July 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711060118/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/fantasy-and-reality-clash-as-movie-makers-film-wonder-woman-in-dc/2018/07/07/4f044522-8215-11e8-b9a5-7e1c013f8c33_story.html|archive-date=July 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> By mid-July, production in the United States was completed and moved to England.<ref>{{cite web |last=Annerino |first=Mike |url=https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-pedro-pascal-filming/ |title=Pedro Pascal Heads To London To Film ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |date=July 13, 2018|access-date=July 29, 2018 |work=Heroic Hollywood|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729200532/https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-pedro-pascal-filming/|archive-date=July 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In August, filming on location took place in several places around London, including St. Andrew's Place, [[Regent's Park]] and the [[Royal College of Physicians]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Daniels |first=Omari |url=https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-1984-filming-london/ |title=New Set Photos Reveal ''Wonder Woman 1984'' Now Filming In London |date=August 7, 2018|access-date=August 9, 2018 |work=Heroic Hollywood|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810011451/https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-1984-filming-london/|archive-date=August 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Begley |first=Chris |url=https://batman-news.com/2018/08/09/wonder-woman-1984-to-film-at-royal-college-of-physicians-in-london-photo/ |title=Exclusive: ''Wonder Woman 1984'' to film at Royal College of Physicians in London (photo) |date=August 9, 2018|access-date=August 9, 2018 |work=Batman-News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810011233/https://batman-news.com/2018/08/09/wonder-woman-1984-to-film-at-royal-college-of-physicians-in-london-photo/|archive-date=August 10, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Between September and October 2018, production also took place at Almer\u00eda, in Andalusia, southern Spain,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.europapress.es/andalucia/almeria-00350/noticia-alcazaba-acogera-rodaje-varias-escenas-wonder-woman-1984-septiembre-20180828153022.html |title=La Alcazaba acoger\u00e1 el rodaje de varias escenas de ''Wonder Woman: 1984'' en septiembre |location=Almer\u00eda |date=August 28, 2018 |access-date=August 29, 2018 |newspaper=[[Europa Press (news agency)|Europa Press]] |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828152940/http://www.europapress.es/andalucia/almeria-00350/noticia-alcazaba-acogera-rodaje-varias-escenas-wonder-woman-1984-septiembre-20180828153022.html |archive-date=August 28, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.diariodealmeria.es/ocio/rodaje-Wonder-Woman-Alcazaba-septiembre_0_1277272371.html |title=El rodaje de ''Wonder Woman: 1984'' ser\u00e1 en la Alcazaba del 5 al 8 de septiembre |first=D. |last=Mart\u00ednez |date=August 29, 2018 |access-date=August 29, 2018 |newspaper=[[Diario de Almer\u00eda]] |language=es |publisher=[[Joly Digital]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829175350/https://www.diariodealmeria.es/ocio/rodaje-Wonder-Woman-Alcazaba-septiembre_0_1277272371.html |archive-date=August 29, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> as well as Fuerteventura and Tenerife in the Canary Islands.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/el-rodaje-de-wonder-woman-desembarca-a-finales-del-verano-MH4584385 |title=El rodaje de ''Wonder Woman'' desembarca a finales del verano |last=Monserrat |first=David |date=May 19, 2018 |publisher=Canarias7 (in Spanish)|access-date=May 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522042253/https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/el-rodaje-de-wonder-woman-desembarca-a-finales-del-verano-MH4584385|archive-date=May 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.guidetocanaryislands.com/tenerife-will-be-one-of-the-filming-locations-for-the-next-wonder-woman-movie/ |title=Tenerife will be one of the filming locations for the next Wonder Woman movie |date=April 20, 2018 |accessdate=May 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143205/https://www.guidetocanaryislands.com/tenerife-will-be-one-of-the-filming-locations-for-the-next-wonder-woman-movie/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> From September 5 to 11, filming occurred at the [[Alcazaba of Almer\u00eda]] fortified complex and the Wall of Jayran in Almer\u00eda.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cope.es/actualidad/cultura/noticias/alcazaba-almeria-acogera-septiembre-parte-rodaje-wonder-woman-1984-20180828_252883 |title=Alcazaba de Almer\u00eda acoger\u00e1 en septiembre parte rodaje ''Wonder Woman: 1984'' |date=August 28, 2018 |publisher=COPE (in Spanish) |accessdate=August 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829142505/https://www.cope.es/actualidad/cultura/noticias/alcazaba-almeria-acogera-septiembre-parte-rodaje-wonder-woman-1984-20180828_252883|archive-date=August 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Production moved to Fuerteventura from September 13 through September 26, with the Corralejo Dunes National Park, Parque Holand\u00e9s, El Jablito, La Oliva and the Jand\u00eda Natural Park as filming locations.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/una-superproduccion-para-fuerteventura-FI3965430 |title=Una superproducci\u00f3n para Fuerteventura |last=Monserrat |first=David |date=March 25, 2018 |publisher=Canarias7 (in Spanish)|access-date=May 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180325124824/https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/una-superproduccion-para-fuerteventura-FI3965430|archive-date=March 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/wonder-woman-1984-arranca-el-rodaje-el-jueves-13-hasta-el-dia-25-BE5457131 |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' arranca el rodaje el Jueves 13 hasta el dia 25 |date=September 11, 2018 |publisher=Canarias7 (in Spanish) |accessdate=September 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911092206/https://www.canarias7.es/siete-islas/fuerteventura/wonder-woman-1984-arranca-el-rodaje-el-jueves-13-hasta-el-dia-25-BE5457131|archive-date=September 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Filming in Tenerife began during the last week of September, lasting two weeks at various different locations on the island.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thinkspain.com/news-spain/30917/wonder-woman-1984-to-be-filmed-in-tenerife |title=Wonder Woman 1984 to be filmed in Tenerife |date=August 28, 2018 |publisher=thinkSPAIN |accessdate=September 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903045916/https://www.thinkspain.com/news-spain/30917/wonder-woman-1984-to-be-filmed-in-tenerife|archive-date=September 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.laopinion.es/cultura/2018/09/02/productora-islena-sur-film-trabajara/906706.html |title=La productora isle\u00f1a Sur Film trabajar\u00e1 en el rodaje en Espa\u00f1a de ''Wonder Woman'' |date=September 2, 2018 |publisher=La Opini\u00f3n de Tenefife (in Spanish) |accessdate=September 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180902121332/https://www.laopinion.es/cultura/2018/09/02/productora-islena-sur-film-trabajara/906706.html|archive-date=September 2, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nProduction went back to England in October, with shooting on location taking place at the [[Imperial War Museum Duxford|Imperial War Museum]] in Duxford, [[Hyde Park, London|Hyde Park]] and the Savoy Hotel in Central London, and [[Torrington Square]], adjacent to Birkbeck, University of London.{{cn|date=February 2020}} By mid-November 2018, [[Pedro Pascal]] finished filming his scenes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/star-wars-pedro-pascal-mandalorian-series-1203023818/ |title=''Star Wars'': Pedro Pascal to Lead ''The Mandalorian'' Series |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=November 13, 2018 |publisher=Variety |access-date=November 14, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114000343/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/star-wars-pedro-pascal-mandalorian-series-1203023818/ |archive-date=November 14, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> Principal photography wrapped on December 22, 2018, after a six-month shoot.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-1984-wrap-december/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' To Wrap Filming This December |last=Mistroff |first=Michael |date=September 4, 2018 |publisher=HeroicHollywood |access-date=September 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905102049/https://heroichollywood.com/wonder-woman-1984-wrap-december/ |archive-date=September 5, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/wonder-woman-1984-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-warner-bros-dc-1202525495/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'': Gal Gadot Posts Heartfelt Message As Production Wraps |last=Ramos |first=Dino-Ray |date=December 23, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |access-date=December 24, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224041346/https://deadline.com/2018/12/wonder-woman-1984-gal-gadot-patty-jenkins-warner-bros-dc-1202525495/ |archive-date=December 24, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> Additional photography began on July 28, 2019, in London at Warner Bros. Studios,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/amp/2019/07/28/wonder-woman-1984-movie-spoilers-2020-reshoots-dceu/ |title=Wonder Woman 1984 Reportedly Doing Reshoots |date=July 28, 2019|access-date=September 6, 2019 |website=comicbook.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906071050/https://comicbook.com/dc/amp/2019/07/28/wonder-woman-1984-movie-spoilers-2020-reshoots-dceu/|archive-date=September 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and was completed the following month.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.unionjournalism.com/2019/08/12/wonder-woman-1984-re-shooting-wrapped-a-must-read-guide-for-fans/ |title=Wonder Woman 1984: Re-shooting wrapped? A Must Read Guide for Fans!!! |date=August 12, 2019|access-date=February 1, 2020 |website=UnionJournalism.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Post-production ===\n[[Richard Pearson (film editor)|Richard Pearson]] will serve as the editor for ''Wonder Woman 1984''.<ref name=\"Production\"/> John Moffatt (''[[Harry Potter (film series)|Harry Potter]]'' and ''[[Life (2017 film)|Life]]'') will serve as the overall visual effects supervisor for the film.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Marc |first1=Christopher |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' Adds ''Harry Potter and The Deathly Hallows'' VFX Supervisor |url=https://hnentertainment.co/wonder-woman-1984-adds-harry-potter-and-the-deathly-hallows-vfx-supervisor/ |access-date=November 28, 2018 |work=HNEntertainment.co |date=November 28, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129012720/https://hnentertainment.co/wonder-woman-1984-adds-harry-potter-and-the-deathly-hallows-vfx-supervisor/ |archive-date=November 29, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Frei |first1=Vincent |url=https://www.artofvfx.com/wonder-woman-1984/ |title= Wonder Woman 1984/ |work=Art of VFX |date=December 8, 2019|accessdate=December 8, 2019}}</ref> Double Negative ([[DNEG]]), [[Framestore]] and [[Method Studios]] will provide the visual effects for the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dneg.com/show/wonder-woman-1984/ |title=Wonder Woman 1984 |accessdate=January 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102002204/https://www.dneg.com/show/wonder-woman-1984/|archive-date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.framestore.com/work/upcoming-film-releases |title=Framestore upcoming film releases |accessdate=February 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170920092547/https://framestore.com/work/upcoming-film-releases|archive-date=September 20, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.methodstudios.com/en/in-production/ |title=Method Studios Features & Episodics In Production |accessdate=May 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190511141707/https://www.methodstudios.com/en/in-production/|archive-date=May 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Alexis Wajsbrot]] is serving as the visual effects supervisor for Framestore.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Frei |first1=Vincent |url=https://www.artofvfx.com/spider-man-far-from-home-alexis-wajsbrot-vfx-supervisor-framestore/ |title=Spider-man \u2013 Far From Home: Alexis Wasjbrot \u2013 VFX Supervisor \u2013 Framestore |work=Art of VFX |date=July 16, 2019|accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> In December 2019, Jenkins revealed work on the film was completed five months in advance of the original release date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487309/wonder-woman-1984-is-technically-done-and-heres-the-first-cuts-runtime|title=Wonder Woman 1984 Is 'Technically Done' And Here's The First Cut's Runtime|date=December 21, 2019|website=CINEMABLEND}}</ref>\n\n== Music ==\nOn August 22, 2018, [[Hans Zimmer]] was announced as the composer for ''Wonder Woman 1984'', replacing [[Rupert Gregson-Williams]] who scored the first film. Zimmer previously scored ''[[Man of Steel (film)|Man of Steel]]'' and ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'', the first and second films in the [[DC Extended Universe]].<ref name=\"Zimmer\">{{cite web |title=Hans Zimmer to Score Patty Jenkins' ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/22/hans-zimmer-to-score-patty-jenkins-wonder-woman-1984/ |work=Film Music Reporter|access-date=August 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181002023825/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/22/hans-zimmer-to-score-patty-jenkins-wonder-woman-1984/|archive-date=October 2, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''Wonder Woman 1984'' is scheduled to be released by Warner Bros. Pictures in the United States in RealD 3D, Dolby Cinema, and IMAX 3D{{citation needed|date=March 2020}} on August 14, 2020.<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date August\"/> It was originally announced for December 13, 2019,<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date December\">{{cite web |last1=Galuppo |first1=Mia |last2=Shanley |first2=Patrick |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Sets Release Date |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-2-release-date-set-1022782 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=July 26, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170726024056/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-2-release-date-set-1022782 |archivedate=July 26, 2017}}</ref> and then moved to November 1, 2019,<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date November\">{{cite web |last1=McClintock |first1=Pamela |title=''Wonder Woman 2'' Release Date Moved Up 6 Weeks |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-2-release-date-moves-up-6-weeks-1057572 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=June 16, 2018 |date=November 13, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616153408/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-2-release-date-moves-up-6-weeks-1057572 |archive-date=June 16, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> then to June 5, 2020.<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date June\">{{cite news |first1=Anthony |last1=D'Alessandro |accessdate=October 22, 2018 |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' Flies To Summer 2020 |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/wonder-woman-1984-flies-to-summer-2020-1202487260/ |newspaper=Deadline |date=October 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181022213802/https://deadline.com/2018/10/wonder-woman-1984-flies-to-summer-2020-1202487260/|archive-date=October 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On March 24, 2020, the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] led to the film [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema|being delayed]] until August 14, 2020.<ref name=\"WW2 Release Date August\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-1984-release-pushed-coronavirus-concerns-1284285|title='Wonder Woman 1984' Release Pushed to Late Summer Amid Coronavirus Pandemic|first1=Mia|last1=Galuppo|first2=Pamela|last2=McClintock|date=March 24, 2020|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324190613/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-1984-release-pushed-coronavirus-concerns-1284285|archive-date=March 24, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nLike its predecessor, ''Wonder Woman 1984'' will not be shown in several Arab and Muslim nations due to Gadot's past as an [[Israel Defense Forces|Israeli soldier]] and the enforcement of the [[Arab League boycott of Israel|Israeli boycott]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stepfeed.com/egyptian-actor-criticized-for-taking-acting-role-with-israel-s-gal-gadot-4487|title=Egyptian actor criticized for taking 'acting role' with Israel's Gal Gadot|first=Rayana|last=Khalaf|date=November 19, 2019|website=StepFeed}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing==\n[[File:Patty Jenkins, Chris Pine & Gal Gadot at the 2018 Comic-Con International 3.jpg|thumb|[[Patty Jenkins]], [[Chris Pine]], and [[Gal Gadot]] promoting ''Wonder Woman 1984'' at the 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]]]\n\nOn June 22, 2018, it was reported that Gal Gadot would be attending Warner Bros.' DC presentation at the 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con]] (SDCC), and some footage from the film would be shown to promote it.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/wonder-woman-comic-con-surprise-gal-gadot-footage-warner-bros-aquaman-1202414752/ |title=Gal Gadot and ''Wonder Woman 1984'' Planned As Warner's Big Comic-Con Surprise |first1=Anthony |last1=D'Alessandro |first2=Dominic |last2=Patten |date=June 21, 2018 |work=Deadline|access-date=June 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622193041/https://deadline.com/2018/06/wonder-woman-comic-con-surprise-gal-gadot-footage-warner-bros-aquaman-1202414752/|archive-date=June 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Director [[Patty Jenkins]] and actors Gadot and [[Chris Pine]] attended the ''Wonder Woman 1984'' panel at SDCC on July 21, 2018, where a short clip of the film was shown.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/wonder-woman-1984-patty-jenkins-gal-gadot-chris-pine-comic-con-1202880369/ |title=''Wonder Woman 1984'' Team Talks '80s Setting, Chris Pine's Resurrection |first1=Erin |last=Nyren |date=July 21, 2018 |work=Variety|access-date=August 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828170110/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/wonder-woman-1984-patty-jenkins-gal-gadot-chris-pine-comic-con-1202880369/|archive-date=August 28, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> New footage was shown during [[ShoWest Convention|CinemaCon]] 2019 in Las Vegas, Nevada, with a first look at Kristen Wiig in the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/04/03/wonder-woman-1984-footage-shown-at-cinemacon-includes-first-look-at-kristen-wiig-cheetah |title=Wonder Woman 1984 Footage Shown at CinemaCon Includes First Look at Kristen Wiig |first1=Jim |last=Vejvoda|date=April 4, 2019 |work=IGN|access-date=October 27, 2019}}</ref> In June 2019, Warner Bros. screened an extended look to European exhibitors at [[CineEurope]] in Barcelona, Spain.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/warner-bros-previews-joker-wonder-woman-1984-birds-prey-1218951 |title=CineEurope: Warner Bros. Offers Glimpses of 'Joker', 'Wonder Woman 1984', 'Godzilla vs. Kong' and 'Birds of Prey'|first1=Jennifer |last=Green |date=June 17, 2019 |work=TheHollywoodReporter |access-date=November 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA teaser poster debuted on June 5, 2019, one year ahead of the film's release date.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/06/05/patty-jenkin-and-gal-gadot-debut-first-poster-for-wonder-woman-1984/#56ad482b38dc |title=Gal Gadot And Patty Jenkins Debut First Poster For ''Wonder Woman 1984'' |first1=Scott |last=Mendelson |date=June 5, 2019 |work=Forbes|access-date=June 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606161401/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/06/05/patty-jenkin-and-gal-gadot-debut-first-poster-for-wonder-woman-1984/#56ad482b38dc|archive-date=June 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2019, it was announced that the film's first trailer would debut during [[Comic Con Experience]] CCXP 2019 on December 8, with Gal Gadot and director Patty Jenkins attending the event in S\u00e3o Paulo, Brazil.<ref name=\"WW84-CCXP\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20191021005733/en/Gal-Gadot-Director-Patty-Jenkins-Set-Give |title='Gal Gadot & Director Patty Jenkins Set to Give CCXP Brazil Attendees an Unforgettable Finale With a Special Showcase for Wonder Woman 1984 That Will Close the Con With a Bang and Kick Off the Countdown to the Film\u2019s 2020 Release |date=October 21, 2019 |work=BusinessWire|access-date=October 21, 2019}}</ref> By the end of the month, [[WarnerMedia]] Entertainment debuted new footage from the film during the [[HBO Max]] presentation to the press.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/10/30/wonder-woman-1984-white-house-fight-footage-scene |title=Wonder Woman 1984: New Footage Shows Diana Fighting Inside the White House |first1=Jesse |last1=Schedeen|date=October 30, 2019 |work=IGN |access-date=October 31, 2019}}</ref> The first trailer debuted on December 8 at the 2019 Comic Con Experience (CCXP), with the show being livestreamed on Twitter around the world in real time.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/wonder-woman-1984-trailer-gal-gadot-kristen-wiig-1203427630/ |title=\"'Wonder Woman 1984' Trailer: Gal Gadot Returns With Pedro Pascal, Kristen Wiig |first1=Lorraine |last1=Wheat|date=December 8, 2019 |work=Variety |access-date=December 8, 2019}}</ref> Trailer music theme is Sebastian B\u00f6hm's instrumental remix of \"[[Blue Monday (New Order song)|Blue Monday]]\" by [[New Order (band)|New Order]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sfM7_JLk-84|title=Wonder Woman 1984 \u2013 Official Trailer}}</ref> The same day, [[Film poster#Character posters|character posters]] for Wonder Woman, [[Maxwell Lord]], [[Cheetah (comics)#Barbara Ann Minerva|Barbara Ann Minerva]] and [[Steve Trevor]] were released.<ref>{{cite news |last1= Adler |first1= Matthew |title= Wonder Woman 1984 Character Posters Reveal First Look at Kristen Wiig as Cheetah |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/08/wonder-woman-1984-first-look-kristen-wiig-cheetah-revealed-poster |accessdate=December 9, 2019 |work= IGN|date=December 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Future==\n===Sequel===\nIn January 2019, after principal photography on ''Wonder Woman 1984'' was completed, director and co-writer Patty Jenkins announced that the plot for a third ''Wonder Woman'' film is currently mapped out.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/01/patty-jenkins-interview-i-am-the-night-wonder-woman |title=''Wonder Woman'' Director Patty Jenkins on Her New TV Drama I Am the Night |first=Joy |last=Press |website=HWD |accessdate=January 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190127150040/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/01/patty-jenkins-interview-i-am-the-night-wonder-woman|archive-date=January 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The filmmaker stated that the plot of the next installment would take place during the modern day.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-3-will-not-be-set-past-says-director-patty-jenkins-1179511 |title=Director Patty Jenkins: ''Wonder Woman 3'' Will Be a 'Contemporary Story' |first=Aaron |last=Couch |date=January 26, 2019 |website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=January 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128135222/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-3-will-not-be-set-past-says-director-patty-jenkins-1179511|archive-date=January 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> By December 2019, Jenkins expressed that the wait between the second and third films will be longer than the time it took to release the first sequel.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://heroichollywood.com/patty-jenkins-gal-gadot-wonder-woman-3-plans/ |title=Patty Jenkins Already Has The Story Planned For Gal Gadot\u2019s \u2018Wonder Woman 3\u2019 |first= Sebastian |last= Peris |date=December 9, 2019 |website=Heroic Hollywood|access-date=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Spin-off===\nIn December 2019, director Patty Jenkins announced that a ''Wonder Woman'' spin-off film is in development, with the story focusing on the [[Amazons (DC Comics)|Amazons]] of [[Themyscira (DC Comics)|Themyscira]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/wonder-woman-director-patty-jenkins-considering-amazon-spinoff-1260683|title= 'Wonder Woman' Director Patty Jenkins Considering Amazon Spinoff |website=The Hollywood Reporter| last= McMillan | first=Graeme |date=December 9, 2019| accessdate=December 9, 2019}}</ref> Jenkins is attached as executive producer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newsarama.com/48175-jenkins-developing-wonder-woman-spin-off-for-the-amazons-report.html |title=Jenkins Developing Wonder Woman Spin-Off for the Amazons - Report |last=Arrant |first=Chris |website=[[Newsarama]] |date=December 9, 2019 |access-date=December 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q33408623|c=Category:Wonder Woman 1984|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|s=no|q=no|species=no|wikt=no|display=''Wonder Woman 1984''}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title}}\n* {{Mojo title}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes}}\n* {{Metacritic film}}\n\n{{Wonder Woman}}\n{{Wonder Woman in popular media}}\n{{DC Extended Universe}}\n{{DC Comics films}}\n{{Patty Jenkins}}\n{{Portal bar|Film|United States|Speculative fiction}}\n\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020s action films]]\n[[Category:2020s feminist films]]\n[[Category:2020s sequel films]]\n[[Category:2020s superhero films]]\n[[Category:2020s fantasy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:American superhero films]]\n[[Category:Atlas Entertainment films]]\n[[Category:Cold War films]]\n[[Category:DC Extended Universe films]]\n[[Category:Films based on Greco-Roman mythology]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Patty Jenkins]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Zack Snyder]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1984]]\n[[Category:Films set in London]]\n[[Category:Films set in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Films set in the White House]]\n[[Category:Films shot in the Canary Islands]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hertfordshire]]\n[[Category:Films shot in London]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Spain]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Virginia]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:IMAX films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Patty Jenkins]]\n[[Category:Superheroine films]]\n[[Category:Superhero films featuring female antagonists]]\n[[Category:Upcoming IMAX films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming sequel films]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. films]]\n[[Category:Wonder Woman films]]\n", "name_user": "Gatitoamr12", "label": "safe", "co