{"title_page": "Prymary Colorz", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n|name                  = Prymary Colorz\n|image                   = \n|caption              = \n|background            = group_or_band\n|years_active          = 2000 &ndash; 2004\n|origin                = [[Tampa, Florida]]<ref>http://www.myspace.com/prymarycolorz</ref>\n|genre                 = [[Hip hop music|Hip-hop]], [[R&B]], [[Pop music|Pop]]\n|website                   = \n|label                 = Big 3 Records\n|current_members       = \n|past_members          = Marcus Dilley<br/>Jonathan Thomas<br/>Raj Nichols<br/>Josh Royals\n|associated_acts       = \n}}\n\n'''Prymary Colorz''' was an [[Race (classification of human beings)|interracial]] [[R&B]] music group. The group is composed of members Marcus Dilley, Jonathan Thomas, Raj Nichols and Josh Royals.\n\nThe group released one album, ''If You Only Knew'' with producers like Rodney (Darkchild) Jerkins, John and Dino Elephante, Robin Thicke, and featuring guest singer such as Vickie Winans; its title track peaked at #1 on the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Singles Sales]] chart<ref>{{Harvnb | Whitburn | 2004 | p=461 | Ref=none}}</ref> and #78 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart.<ref>http://www.billboard.com/artist/353940/prymary+colorz/chart</ref> It has been their most successful single to date. \n\nIn 2003, they contributed to the song \"My Perfect Friend\" from the [[Randy Savage]] studio album, ''[[Be a Man  (Randy Savage album)|Be a Man]]''.<ref>https://www.amazon.com/Perfect-Friend-feat-Prymary-Colorz/dp/B0146RZUY8</ref> \n\nThe group disbanded in 2004.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n*2002: ''If You Only Knew'' #61 U.S. [[Hot R&B/Hip-hop albums|R&B Albums]]<ref>{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=prymary colorz|chart=all}}</ref>\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"|Year\n!valign=\"top\"|Song\n!valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"|<small>[[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|U.S.<br/>R&B]]</small>\n!valign=\"top\" 